{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|144","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":144,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":1,"text":"Blessed be the Lord, my rock who trains my hands for battle and my fingers for warfare.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":2,"text":"He is my faithful love and my fortress, my stronghold and my deliverer. He is my shield, and I take refuge in him; he subdues my people under me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":3,"text":"Lord, what is a human that you care for him, a son of man that you think of him?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":4,"text":"A human is like a breath; his days are like a passing shadow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":5,"text":"Lord, part your heavens and come down. Touch the mountains, and they will smoke.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":6,"text":"Flash your lightning and scatter the foe; shoot your arrows and rout them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":7,"text":"Reach down from on high; rescue me from deep water, and set me free from the grasp of foreigners","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":8,"text":"whose mouths speak lies, whose right hands are deceptive.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":9,"text":"God, I will sing a new song to you; I will play on a ten-stringed harp for you —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":10,"text":"the one who gives victory to kings, who frees his servant David from the deadly sword.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":11,"text":"Set me free and rescue me from foreigners whose mouths speak lies, whose right hands are deceptive.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":12,"text":"Then our sons will be like plants nurtured in their youth, our daughters, like corner pillars that are carved in the palace style.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":13,"text":"Our storehouses will be full, supplying all kinds of produce; our flocks will increase by thousands and tens of thousands in our open fields.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:144:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":144,"verse":14,"text":"Our cattle will be well fed. There will be no breach in the walls, no going into captivity, and no cry of lament in our public squares.","textRevision":